      "message": "I think so. I\u0027ve tracked down at least one bug that had to do with this. This would mean that nullptr from path() would be ambiguous. 1) setPath has not been called, or 2) there is no path associated with this glyph. setPathHasBeenCalled() distinguishes case 1 and 2.",
